━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
WHAT IS A FACT
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

A fact is a coherent unit of information a reader needs to understand one topic.
It is not one sentence or one bullet. It is as much content as belongs together.

  • A fact may contain a title, multiple paragraphs, a bullet list, a table, or any mix.
  • A local heading (bold text, ##, etc.) is the title of a fact, not a boundary between
    facts. Include it as part of the fact's content.
  • The narrative "why" (rationale, values, context) belongs in the same fact as the
    "what" (rules, procedures, details) it motivates. Never separate them.
  • A reader must be able to understand the fact without seeing neighbouring facts.
    Include enough context — do not rely on the reader inferring it from surrounding text.

Target size: 300–2000 characters (soft guide, not a hard limit).
  — Below 300 chars usually means related content was split unnecessarily.
  — Above 2000 chars usually means two distinct topics were merged.

SPLIT only when content clearly shifts to a different concept.
DO NOT split a heading from the body it introduces.
DO NOT split narrative context from the rules it explains.
DO NOT split a list from its introductory sentence or heading.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
EXAMPLES
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

GOOD — one fact covering a full topic with rationale + practical details:

  # 4. Pedagogical Meetings

  We believe it is essential for the family and the school to be aligned on key
  educational guidelines. To facilitate this, we will invite families to quarterly
  meetings between families and educators, where various topics of interest will be
  discussed. These meetings are important for understanding the school's pedagogical
  approach, so we recommend that at least one member from each family attends. They
  offer an opportunity for families to ask questions, share experiences, make
  suggestions, and become more involved in the development of our students.

  We will provide sufficient advance notice so families can reserve these dates in
  their personal calendars.

  To better accommodate families' work-life balance, sessions will be offered both
  in person and online, making this resource accessible to as many families as
  possible. While the online option is very convenient, in-person sessions are more
  enriching due to the practical component that allows participation in group
  dynamics and provides a setting conducive to interaction among families.

  Sessions will be conducted in both languages in separate sessions to ensure the
  inclusion of all families in this process.

  → ONE fact. Type: principle. render_as: paragraph.
    The whole section — rationale + logistics + format — belongs together.

BAD — splitting a list from its header:

  fact 1: "Not acceptable clothing:"          ← heading stripped from its list
  fact 2: "Mini-skirts, hot pants, or lycra…" ← bullet orphaned from context
  fact 3: "Leisure shorts, tracksuits…"       ← same

GOOD — one fact keeping the header + all bullets together:

  fact: "**Not acceptable:** Mini-skirts, hot pants, or lycra cycling shorts shorter
  than mid-thigh. / Leisure shorts, tracksuits, or sportswear (except PE). / ..."
  → ONE fact. Type: rule. render_as: bullet.

